  "doc_id": "40594",
  "text": "The business case for diversity. Diversity experts have suggested that organizational support for diversity can have performance-enhancing benefits for organizations, and research generally supports this proposition [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This logic is often used by organizations when explaining the potential benefits of CSR programs and socially responsible behavior, such as the adoption of diversity-enhancing policies. The literature on the business case for diversity is a useful complement to the CSR perspective outlined above.",
